
) Install Server from CD
Note: don't change anything else
hostname:     server.local
root passwd:  redhat
grub passwd:  redhat
Disk: RAID1

username: kadr
passwd:   123

) On Server as root:
)) turn off selinux
setenforce 0 && \
sed -i "s/SELINUX=.*/SELINUX=permissive/" /etc/sysconfig/selinux
sestatus
reboot
)) Run:
./install_server.sh

) Set BIOS on Terminals
turn on booting from PXE
reboot

) URL for installing through PXE:
http://192.168.1.1/repos/os
turn off IPv6

) Installing settings for Terminals:
hostname:     terminal1.local
              terminal2.local
              terminal<x>.local
root passwd:  redhat
grub passwd:  redhat

username: term1
          term2
passwd:   123

) On Terminals as root:
)) turn off selinux
setenforce 0 && \
sed -i "s/SELINUX=.*/SELINUX=permissive/" /etc/sysconfig/selinux
sestatus
reboot
)) Run:
./install_client.sh

) Turn off PXE on Server
In /etc/dchpd.conf comment follow lines:
  - with pxelinux.0
  - next-server
  - boot*
